Download logo The Minister of Transport, Mr Fikile Mbalula, has noted the judgement handed down by Judge Basson at the Pretoria High Court on 13 January 2022 declaring the Administrative Adjudication of Road Traffic Offences Act and its subsequent Amendment Act unconstitutional and invalid.  The Minister is studying the judgement and will be guided by legal advice on whether to appeal the judgement or not. Distributed by APO Group on behalf of Republic of South Africa: Department of Transport.